# Project Guidance

Use @AGENTS.md as the canonical source for repository architecture, commands,
domain constraints, documentation routing, and verification expectations.

Do not duplicate those rules in Cursor-specific files. Update `AGENTS.md` when a
shared, durable rule changes; add another scoped `.mdc` rule only when a
directory or file pattern genuinely needs additional context.
